Haystack Dependency Injection Documentation
Introduction
The Haystack Dependency Injection package simplifies managing dependencies in Unity
projects. This guide provides an overview of setup, key attributes, and example implementations.
Key Attributes
 [Haystack.Inject]: Marks fields to be injected with dependencies.
 [Haystack.Install]: Marks fields to be installed with dependencies.
 [Haystack.DirectHayClass]: Indicates that the class uses direct injection with tags or keys.
 [Haystack.PhysicsClass]: Specifies that the class handles physics-related injections.
Direct Injection Overview
Direct Injection in Haystack allows you to specify dependencies directly in your Unity scripts
using tags or keys. This method is straightforward and useful for cases where you need to
explicitly define which dependencies should be injected into your components
